sign Home Security";s:3:"alt";s:158:"has your garage door stopped closing have you ever had your garage door randomly stop closing and the ligh home security tips garage door design home security";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/5c/7b/89/5c7b899cf118f46662681a24a804b9ab.png";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTixELnDl7nqvoEjHQqZwqLKljtN5INnfyKFeL2fc2qXz2aRpqN1zCeeIsP-MojnA267bo";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"png";s:5:"width";i:343;s:6:"height";i:568;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://fi.pinterest.com/pin/488077678336569619/";s:6:"domain";s:16:"fi.pinterest.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:42:"garage door opener keeps opening by itself";s:4:"slug";s:42:"garage-door-opener-keeps-opening-by-itself";s:5:"title";s:60:"My Garage Door Will Open Or Close By Itself American Veteran";s:3:"alt";s:29:"american veteran garage doors";s:3:"url";s:113:"https://mygaragedoorrepairlasvegas.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/My-Garage-Door-Will-Open-or-Close-by-Itself.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRsbhgEuE5dVJGfo9sAXHXhAhrlqOXRm7kElw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:500;s:6:"height";i:1400;s:6:"source";s:74:"https://mygaragedoorrepairlasvegas.com/garage-door-will-open-close-itself/";s:6:"domain";s:30:"mygaragedoorrepairlasvegas.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:51:{i:0;s:70:"Yes its possible although rare for your garage door to open by itself.";i:1;s:42:"Here are a few scenarios weve come across.";i:2;s:144:"Residential electric garage door openers manufactured after 1993 are equipped with two safety mechanisms that operate while the door is closing.";i:3;s:156:"How to fix the garage door when it opens by itselfSuddenly my garage door was opening on its own at least couple times a day it starter when i tried to set.";i:4;s:63:"My Lift master garage door would just open up late at night an.";i:5;s:94:"This video will show you how I fixed my garage door from opening by itself seemingly randomly.";i:6;s:101:"A garage door that randomly opens by itself is not a common problem but does occur from time to time.";i:7;s:161:"Garage door openers operate on one of many frequencies and while it is possible for one of your neighbors remotes to open your garage door it is highly unlikely.";i:8;s:86:"Newer openers operate on rolling codes making it almost impossible for this to happen.";i:9;s:50:"Try changing the batteries in your remote control.";i:10;s:118:"Worn batteries have been responsible for sending random signals that cause the garage door to open and close randomly.";i:11;s:75:"Garage door openers built after 1993 have an automatic reversing mechanism.";i:12;s:168:"The remedy is as KennethR did clear all devices from your garage door by holding the learn button for 30 seconds -and reprogram all of your openers to your garage door.";i:13;s:86:"And check that no neighbors are opening their doors when your programming you openers.";i:14;s:92:"Another easy way to fix a garage door that opens by itself is by checking the remote opener.";i:15;s:100:"If the remote opener is dirty or the batteries are failing it may cause the door to open on its own.";i:16;s:110:"Double check their position or change them out to see if it prevents your garage door from opening on its own.";i:17;s:107:"There is no keypad so its not that so it would have to be an RF remote the button inside the garage or MyQ.";i:18;s:55:"I cleared the wifi settings on the opener just in case.";i:19;s:103:"Im going to set up a camera in the garage for a few days to monitor if it still opens when Im not here.";i:20;s:74:"I would hope that another residents remote isnt opening my garage somehow.";i:21;s:141:"The symptom of this is a garage door that is in constant motion opening fully then immediately descending only to start the same cycle again.";i:22;s:74:"There may also be loose wire connections inside the button housing itself.";i:23;s:99:"As these wires short against the housing the electrical impulse causes the door opener to activate.";i:24;s:97:"It could be in the circuit board a remote the wall button or its wiring or even the wired keypad.";i:25;s:124:"Older Stanley garage door openers are known for opening and closing by themselves because of a malfunctioning circuit board.";i:26;s:89:"Defective remotes or ones with worn-out batteries will sometimes send out random signals.";i:27;s:24:"Check the Remote Opener.";i:28;s:92:"Another easy way to fix a garage door that opens by itself is by checking the remote opener.";i:29;s:100:"If the remote opener is dirty or the batteries are failing it may cause the door to open on its own.";i:30;s:82:"The remotes batteries may be breaking down or may just not be positioned properly.";i:31;s:38:"Double check their position or change.";i:32;s:57:"Reasons Why Your Garage Door Keeps Opening After Closing.";i:33;s:96:"If your garage door keeps going back up after youve closed it the most common reason is because.";i:34;s:31:"The safety sensors are blocked.";i:35;s:59:"There are safety sensors at the bottom of your garage door.";i:36;s:67:"This infrared sensor passes a beam horizontally across the opening.";i:37;s:62:"If anything enters the beam even briefly the door opens again.";i:38;s:19:"Garage Door Opener.";i:39;s:27:"Opens and closes by itself.";i:40;s:162:"When your garage door opens or closes when you havent triggered the remote one possible cause is that a neighbors remote was programmed at the same time as yours.";i:41;s:53:"Erase all codes in your remote and then reprogram it.";i:42;s:180:"Garage door is opening and closing fixing mon garage door opener problems liftmaster garage door remote control garage door opens by itself why is my garage door opening by itself.";i:43;s:64:"Neighbor S 1 2 Hp Craftsman Garage Door Opener Keeps Opening By.";i:44;s:38:"Why Does My Garage Door Open Randomly.";i:45;s:45:"7 Reasons To Replace Your Garage Door Opener.";i:46;s:109:"These can damage the transmitters electrical wiring and cause the garage door opener to open at random times.";i:47;s:108:"If a lightning storm has damaged the electrical circuits youll likely need the assistance of a professional.";i:48;s:60:"For a quick professional inspection call us at 503 730-0444.";i:49;s:144:"When a garage door opens on its own the issue might be a loose wire in the motor or the sensor may be stopping the door from closing completely.";i:50;s:87:"Other things to look for are bare or pierced wires and damaged casing around the motor.";}}